🧩 AddArtifact.jsx (React Component)

jsx
import { useState } from "react";
import Swal from "sweetalert2";

const AddArtifact = ({ user }) => {
  const [formData, setFormData] = useState({
    name: "",
    image: "",
    type: "Tools",
    context: "",
    description: "",
    createdAt: "",
    discoveredAt: "",
    discoveredBy: "",
    location: "",
    addedBy: user.name,
    addedByEmail: user.email,
    likes: 0,
  });

  const handleChange = (e) => {
    const { name, value } = e.target;
    setFormData((prev) => ({ ...prev, [name]: value }));
  };

  const handleSubmit = async (e) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    try {
      // Replace with your API endpoint
      const res = await fetch("/api/artifacts", {
        method: "POST",
        headers: { "Content-Type": "application/json" },
        body: JSON.stringify(formData),
      });

      if (res.ok) {
        Swal.fire({
          icon: "success",
          title: "Artifact Added!",
          text: "The artifact has been successfully added to the database.",
          confirmButtonColor: "#e2b13c",
        });
        setFormData((prev) => ({
          ...prev,
          name: "",
          image: "",
          type: "Tools",
          context: "",
          description: "",
          createdAt: "",
          discoveredAt: "",
          discoveredBy: "",
          location: "",
          likes: 0,
        }));
      }
    } catch (error) {
      console.error("Error:", error);
    }
  };

  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-color-base-200 py-10 px-4 lg:px-10">
      <div className="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white shadow-lg rounded-lg p-8">
        <h2 className="text-3xl font-bold text-color-black mb-6 border-b pb-4">
          Add a New Artifact
        </h2>
        <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          {/* Left column */}
          <div>
            <label className="label">Artifact Name</label>
            <input
              type="text"
              name="name"
              required
              className="input input-bordered w-full"
              value={formData.name}
              onChange={handleChange}
            />

            <label className="label mt-4">Artifact Image URL</label>
            <input
              type="url"
              name="image"
              required
              className="input input-bordered w-full"
              value={formData.image}
              onChange={handleChange}
            />

            <label className="label mt-4">Artifact Type</label>
            <select
              name="type"
              className="select select-bordered w-full"
              value={formData.type}
              onChange={handleChange}
            >
              <option>Tools</option>
              <option>Weapons</option>
              <option>Documents</option>
              <option>Writings</option>
              <option>Jewelry</option>
              <option>Pottery</option>
              <option>Other</option>
            </select>

            <label className="label mt-4">Historical Context</label>
            <textarea
              name="context"
              className="textarea textarea-bordered w-full"
              rows={3}
              value={formData.context}
              onChange={handleChange}
            ></textarea>
          </div>

          {/* Right column */}
          <div>
            <label className="label">Short Description</label>
            <textarea
              name="description"
              className="textarea textarea-bordered w-full"
              rows={3}
              value={formData.description}
              onChange={handleChange}
            ></textarea>

            <label className="label mt-4">Created At</label>
            <input
              type="text"
              name="createdAt"
              className="input input-bordered w-full"
              value={formData.createdAt}
              onChange={handleChange}
              placeholder="e.g., 100 BC"
            />

            <label className="label mt-4">Discovered At</label>
            <input
              type="text"
              name="discoveredAt"
              className="input input-bordered w-full"
              value={formData.discoveredAt}
              onChange={handleChange}
              placeholder="e.g., 1799"
            />

            <label className="label mt-4">Discovered By</label>
            <input
              type="text"
              name="discoveredBy"
              className="input input-bordered w-full"
              value={formData.discoveredBy}
              onChange={handleChange}
            />

            <label className="label mt-4">Present Location</label>
            <input
              type="text"
              name="location"
              className="input input-bordered w-full"
              value={formData.location}
              onChange={handleChange}
            />
          </div>

          {/* Read-only user fields */}
          <div className="md:col-span-2">
            <div className="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div>
                <label className="label">Added By</label>
                <input
                  type="text"
                  className="input input-bordered w-full bg-gray-100"
                  value={formData.addedBy}
                  readOnly
                />
              </div>
              <div>
                <label className="label">Email</label>
                <input
                  type="email"
                  className="input input-bordered w-full bg-gray-100"
                  value={formData.addedByEmail}
                  readOnly
                />
              </div>
            </div>

            {/* Submit Button */}
            <div className="text-right mt-6">
              <button type="submit" className="btn bg-[--color-primary] hover:bg-yellow-500 text-white text-lg">
                Add Artifact
              </button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

export default AddArtifact;

✅ Final Design Code

jsx
import { useState } from 'react';
import { useForm } from 'react-hook-form';
import Swal from 'sweetalert2';
import { useAuth } from '../hooks/useAuth'; // Example custom hook for user info

const AddArtifact = () => {
  const { user } = useAuth(); // Assuming you get name & email from context or hook
  const { register, handleSubmit, reset } = useForm();
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);

  const onSubmit = async (data) => {
    setLoading(true);
    const artifact = {
      ...data,
      likes: 0,
      addedBy: {
        name: user.name,
        email: user.email,
      },
    };

    try {
      // Replace with actual API call
      await fetch('/api/artifacts', {
        method: 'POST',
        headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' },
        body: JSON.stringify(artifact),
      });

      Swal.fire({
        icon: 'success',
        title: 'Artifact Added!',
        text: `${artifact.name} has been successfully added.`,
        background: '#f8f8f8',
        color: '#252930',
        confirmButtonColor: '#e2b13c',
      });

      reset();
    } catch (err) {
      Swal.fire('Error', 'Something went wrong.', 'error');
    } finally {
      setLoading(false);
    }
  };

  return (
    <div className="min-h-screen bg-base-200 py-12 px-4 sm:px-10">
      <div className="max-w-4xl mx-auto bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg p-10 border border-gray-200">
        <h2 className="text-3xl font-bold text-black mb-8 border-b pb-4">
          Add New Artifact
        </h2>
        <form onSubmit={handleSubmit(onSubmit)} className="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <div>
            <label className="label">Artifact Name</label>
            <input {...register('name', { required: true })} className="input input-bordered w-full" placeholder="Rosetta Stone" />
          </div>

          <div>
            <label className="label">Artifact Image (URL)</label>
            <input {...register('image', { required: true })} className="input input-bordered w-full" placeholder="https://..." />
          </div>

          <div>
            <label className="label">Artifact Type</label>
            <select {...register('type')} className="select select-bordered w-full">
              <option>Tools</option>
              <option>Weapons</option>
              <option>Documents</option>
              <option>Writings</option>
              <option>Other</option>
            </select>
          </div>

          <div>
            <label className="label">Historical Context</label>
            <input {...register('context')} className="input input-bordered w-full" placeholder="Used during Roman Empire..." />
          </div>

          <div className="md:col-span-2">
            <label className="label">Short Description</label>
            <textarea {...register('description')} className="textarea textarea-bordered w-full" rows={3}></textarea>
          </div>

          <div>
            <label className="label">Created At</label>
            <input {...register('createdAt')} className="input input-bordered w-full" placeholder="100 BC" />
          </div>

          <div>
            <label className="label">Discovered At</label>
            <input {...register('discoveredAt')} className="input input-bordered w-full" placeholder="1799" />
          </div>

          <div>
            <label className="label">Discovered By</label>
            <input {...register('discoveredBy')} className="input input-bordered w-full" placeholder="Pierre-François Bouchard" />
          </div>

          <div>
            <label className="label">Present Location</label>
            <input {...register('location')} className="input input-bordered w-full" placeholder="British Museum, London" />
          </div>

          <div>
            <label className="label">Your Name</label>
            <input readOnly value={user?.name} className="input input-bordered w-full bg-gray-100" />
          </div>

          <div>
            <label className="label">Your Email</label>
            <input readOnly value={user?.email} className="input input-bordered w-full bg-gray-100" />
          </div>

          <div className="md:col-span-2 text-right">
            <button type="submit" className="btn bg-[#e2b13c] text-white hover:bg-yellow-500" disabled={loading}>
              {loading ? 'Adding...' : 'Add Artifact'}
            </button>
          </div>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
};

export default AddArtifact;

  • Color Theme: Uses your palette: #e2b13c, #252930, etc.

  • Layout: Responsive grid with two columns on large screens.

  • Form Controls: DaisyUI components with Tailwind styling.

  • UX: SweetAlert for success; loading state on button.

ChatGPT said:

To add likeCount (or any additional property) to your artifactInfo object after creating it from FormData, you can simply assign it like this:

js
const handleAddArtifact = (e) => {
  e.preventDefault();
  const form = e.target;
  const formData = new FormData(form);
  const artifactInfo = Object.fromEntries(formData.entries());

  // Add likeCount property
  artifactInfo.likeCount = 0;

  console.log(artifactInfo);
};

✅ Result

Your artifactInfo object will now look like this:

js
{
  name: "Rosetta Stone",

  context: "...",
  description: "...",
  createdAt: "100 BC",
  discoveredAt: "1799",
  discoveredBy: "...",
  location: "...",
  adderName: "...",
  adderEmail: "...",
  likeCount: 0
}
